


	
        2005 end-of-year link blowout sale          Raymond Chen        
            
            January 3rd, 20060 0
		
         A quick list of links amassed over the past year. Not quite worth a posting on their own, but together they might mean something. 

ProFont,     a font for code.     Haven’t tried it out, but it looks intriguing. 
Free     annual credit reports, one per credit reporting agency per year. 
When people assume the system will never change, episode 2:     Grovelling into the internals of .NET classes.     When this code breaks, who will take the blame? 
LR’s guide to the new newswriting:     A quick reference to news cliches. 
The Grand List of Console Role Playing Game Cliches. 
Stupid debugger tricks: Radix conversion. 
Picking up girls can be as easy as opening a beer! 
Living in America:     The culture shock of moving from Germany to Los Angeles.     (Warning: In German.)     Heck, moving from anywhere to Los Angeles     would be a culture shock for most people… 
Crashed cars of Kuwait.     In a country with wide open roads     and little to no speed enforcement,     you wind up with a lot of abandoned crashed cars by the roadside. 
SkiFree,     the classic Windows skiing game.     I never got any good at it.     I wasted my time on     JezzBall instead. 
Rats!  Erm, I mean “Rat!” 

 [While Raymond was on vacation,  the autopilot stopped working due to  a power outage. This entry has been backdated.] 

        
                

        
		
                

            
            
                
